caption: Did not label dishes that had been modified as gluten free for take out on an order of 7 dishes that were partially GF and others regular. Not consistent when we called asking which entrees were gluten free or regular and just insisted that if the receipt was correct then that’s what we got. To me that just indicated that they received the order correctly but no indication that the dishes were correctly modified.  A sharpie marking any indication on the top of the container would have solved this or train the staff to be knowledgeable about the shape of GF pasta used to alleviate any confusion. Marking the containers would have helped even the people that could eat gluten since they couldn’t figure out which dish was which until biting in and then having to trade.  We were told 3 different pasta types it could have been and were told that if it wasn’t a particular pasta it was probably right - not a vote of confidence. They ended up hanging up on me and not offering any alternative or clarification just to come back to the restaurant if we were unhappy.  Cannot recommend for celiac or gluten-free until they amend their processes, particularly for take out. Major disappointment after reading good reviews that this was good for gluten free and perhaps they are but for me attempting to eat the food wasn’t worth the risk of ending up sick for days.

Zero stars! Skip it! My girlfriend and I went to this place to celebrate our birthdays at around 4:00 on a Fri, after work. Place was empty! Walking in the greeter bus boy (?) tried to sit us at a very small table by a wall (2 women...would he do this to 2 men?). My friend asked politely if we could sit at a larger table (for 4) by the window. He reluctantly agreed saying,  "Ok but don't stay too long, you women can talk for four hours, we get really busy tonight."  Welcome to Topo! This should have been enough. Why didn't we leave? After our meal we wanted tea. Our waiter said,  "Just don't take too long..."  My friend asked for the manager. We told him everything. He said,  "Yae it's a busy night" and continued w the get out message. Meanwhile four empty tables, 2 for four people, surrounded us. Then suddenly the waiter came and started to scream in my friend's face,  "What you say to my manager??!! You lied!! Leave my table!! Out!!!"  Other tables were staring. I almost called 911... but he walked away. Then he returned, and screamed from two tables away...  "Didn't you hear me, out!!!"  Umm, we needed to finish our tea, pay, etc. We never did anything. We wanted tea!! We just sat in shock. Dealt w sexism, rudeness, were both highly insulted, and still had a $75.00 bill for two meals, two wines, and tea. Did I mention we have been going to Topo for many yrs. On our way out we passed 2 tables w only 2 people (seating for 4) but they were couples, so probably not harassed.  Goodbye Topo, your days are numbered. We both live and work in the neighborhood. Everyone will hear this story! Crazy!!!!! The most awful, stressful experience. Wells has 50 other restaurants, go next door.  Post note: The Caesar guy who clicked funny is the bartender...pretty sure. The employees at this place think what happened to us is funny. Crazy!  Update- we have been telling everyone what 3 employees were like at this place (1 a manager!) and finding out so many similar stories like this...stay away. Yikes!!! I see a lawsuit soon.

T.G. came highly recommended by some friends, so we figured we'd try it out. Easily made reservations just two days before for dinner at 7:00. We tried the grilled calamari appetizer since we had only ever had fried calamari. It exceeded expectations and came in a delicious sauce. I had the spaghetti and meatballs in a bolognese sauce, and my wife had the corkscrew pasta in a cheesy sauce that came with chicken. She says it is the best pasta dish she has ever had, and mine was on up at the top of my list. They do not have beer, but have a good wine list that is reasonable for a casual wine drinker. The bread and dipping oil was just so-so, but that was appreciated when we had more room for our food! Dessert menu looked good, but we were too full to order one. Our intention was to each have a pasta dish then split an entree since that menu looked so good - especially the veal, chicken, and steak options..., but we were stuffed after our appetizer and pasta dishes. Service was good, and we were well taken care of, and taken to our table right at our reservation time.
